    "extract": "Huntington Ingalls Industries, Inc., (HII) is the largest military shipbuilding company in the United States as well as a provider of professional services to partners in government and industry. HII was formed on March 31, 2011, as a divestiture from  Northrop Grumman.\nHII comprises three divisions: Newport News Shipbuilding in Virginia, Ingalls Shipbuilding in Mississippi, and Mission Technologies.\nIn April 2022, Huntington Ingalls Industries changed its branding name to HII.\n\n"
